Forum of the State Chairmen of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has restated their commitment to party unity adding that it would resist disunity in the New Year. The Forum stated this given the crisis that bedeviled the APC last year. Speaking with some journalists, the chairman of the Forum and Borno State APC chairman, Hon. Ali Bukar Dalori said members of the Forum would not fold their hands and allow the party to fall apart. According to him, the Forum would neither support the Progressive Governors Forum (PGF) or the National Leadership of the party in any wrongdoing or decision but to support President Muhammadu Buhari on the unity of the party. The Forum chairman called on the National Reconciliation Committee chaired by the Senate President, Senator Ahmed Lawan to be fair, impartial and thorough in discharging its duties. He said the Committee’s work would assist in bringing a lasting peace in the party should they do a sincere job. Dalori commended members of the Forum for considering the interest of the party above individual interest. Speaking, Dalori said, “we have to work for the unity of the party. “The Forum of APC State Chairmen would not join things that would disintegrate the party. “As a Forum we are Independent, therefore would not support the PGF or the APC national leadership on any wrongdoing. “As chairmen, we believe much responsibility is placed on our shoulders for the success of our party.” Also speaking, the Forum chairmen said, “l will like to use this opportunity to call on the National Reconciliation Committee to be fair in their assignment of reconciling aggrieved members in the party. “Both high and might should know that if anything happens to APC as a party we all be affected directly or indirectly, therefore we all should be sincere and guide the party.” He used the opportunity to call on President Buhari to engage the Forum more for the growth and unity of the party.